Reasoning: The paper discusses the security implications of speculative execution in CPUs, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves analyzing the inner workings of CPUs (cs.AR) and the potential impact on operating systems (cs.OS). Additionally, the paper discusses the side effects of speculative execution and how it can be used to read arbitrary memory, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and system-level security (cs.SY).
